# Parity Hack #1 / Unauthorized Initialization
Network: Hardhat in-memory simulated network only. No live RPC or wallet used.
WalletLibraryVulnerable: 0x5FbDB2315678afecb367f032d93F642f64180aa3
Deploying three WalletVulnerable proxies that delegatecall to the same library: Wallet 1 is the legitimate-control wallet; Wallets 2 and 3 are exploited.

## Wallet 1: legitimate initialization control
Wallet 1 proxy: 0xe7f1725E7734CE288F8367e1Bb143E90bb3F0512
Wallet 1 balance before init: 5.0 ETH
Owner is owner after legitimate initWallet: true
[assertion ok] Wallet 1 legitimate owner is initialized
Wallet 1 balance after legitimate owner execute(1 ETH): 4.0 ETH
[assertion ok] Wallet 1 remains under legitimate owner control after one normal withdrawal: 4.0 ETH

## Wallet 2: attacker initialization and drain
Wallet 2 proxy: 0x9fE46736679d2D9a65F0992F2272dE9f3c7fa6e0
